<tr id="L383"><td><a href="#L383">383</a></td><td>SPOCK:  A fact, Captain. Physical laws simply cannot be ignored. Existence cannot be without them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L384"><td><a href="#L384">384</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What do you mean, Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L385"><td><a href="#L385">385</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I mean, Doctor, that we are faced with a staggering contradiction. The tranquilliser you created should have been effective.</td></tr>

<tr id="L386"><td><a href="#L386">386</a></td><td>KIRK:  It would've been effective anywhere else.</td></tr>

<tr id="L387"><td><a href="#L387">387</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Exactly. Doctor, in your opinion, what killed Mister Chekov?</td></tr>

<tr id="L388"><td><a href="#L388">388</a></td><td>MCCOY:  A piece of lead in his body.</td></tr>

<tr id="L389"><td><a href="#L389">389</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Wrong. His mind killed him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L390"><td><a href="#L390">390</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Come on, Spock. If you've got the answer, tell us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L391"><td><a href="#L391">391</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Physical reality is consistent with universal laws. Where the laws do not operate, there is no reality. All of this is unreal.</td></tr>

<tr id="L392"><td><a href="#L392">392</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What do you mean unreal? I examined Chekov. He's dead.</td></tr>

<tr id="L393"><td><a href="#L393">393</a></td><td>SPOCK:  But you made your examination under conditions which we cannot trust. We judge reality by the response of our senses. Once we are convinced of the reality of a given situation, we abide by its rules. We judged the bullets to be solid, the guns to be real, therefore they can kill.</td></tr>

<tr id="L394"><td><a href="#L394">394</a></td><td>KIRK:  Chekov is dead because he believed the bullets would kill him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L395"><td><a href="#L395">395</a></td><td>SPOCK:  He may indeed be dead. We do not know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L396"><td><a href="#L396">396</a></td><td>KIRK:  But we do know that the Melkotians created the situation. If we do not allow ourselves to believe that the bullets are real, they cannot kill us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L397"><td><a href="#L397">397</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Exactly. I know the bullets are unreal, therefore they cannot harm me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L398"><td><a href="#L398">398</a></td><td>KIRK:  We must all be as certain as you are, Mister Spock, to save our lives.</td></tr>

<tr id="L399"><td><a href="#L399">399</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Precisely.</td></tr>

<tr id="L400"><td><a href="#L400">400</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But that's not possible. There'd always be some doubt.</td></tr>

<tr id="L401"><td><a href="#L401">401</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The smallest doubt would be enough to kill you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L402"><td><a href="#L402">402</a></td><td>MCCOY:  We're just human beings, Spock. We don't have that clockwork ticker in our head like you do. We can't turn it on and off.</td></tr>

